    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>Structural Description</title>

        <levelledPara>
          <title>Purpose</title>
          <para>The 10-hole fixture pattern secures the BH-STA350 bulkhead to Frame C0. It ensures uniform load distribution and maintains alignment under pressure and vibration.</para>
        </levelledPara>

        <levelledPara>
          <title>Layout</title>
          <para>The pattern consists of ten evenly spaced Hi-Lok fasteners arranged radially around the bulkhead perimeter. Each fastener is indexed to a datum reference and torqued to specification.</para>
        </levelledPara>

        <levelledPara>
          <title>Installation</title>
          <para>Fasteners are installed through pre-drilled holes in the bulkhead flange and Frame C0 web. A torque sequence is followed to prevent warping and ensure concentricity.</para>
        </levelledPara>

        <levelledPara>
          <title>Compliance</title>
          <para>The fixture meets CS-25.603 and CS-25.605 for fastener integrity and installation. It is validated under the BH-STA350_SKEL_VALIDATED badge and referenced in the UTCS registry.</para>
        </levelledPara>

      </levelledPara>
    </description>
